ssibly because the native image doesn't include class$, or the method is inaccessible. Maybe MethodHandles.privateLookupIn needs specific metadata to access private methods, which could lead to failures. I might refine my approach by using Groovy's metaClass public API to invoke the static method, as Groovy can access package-private methods. \\n\\nCould writing a Groovy test help with this?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Reflection and Coverage**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the dynamic agent might only track actual reflection calls made by the application. Invoking class$ with MethodHandle should trigger Class.forName and cover it, but what if the class call got constant folded instead? Hmm, perhaps importing SpecificationMerger is causing the class to initialize earlier, but that shouldn’t be the issue. The \\\"newly covered none\\\" after the second attempt could mean the external evaluation missed my test. It seems like I may need a dedicated Java test file for proper one-to-one mapping.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class initialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about what happens when `Class.forName` is called with an already initialized class. It seems like it should still work. However, I wonder if `RestAssuredConfig` is imported; well, it turns out it's only being used through a string. I should also consider whether the merge test might load `RestAssuredConfig` via the `RequestSpecBuilder` beforehand since the order of JUnit tests isn’t specified. There’s a lot to unpack here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5BRMDkIvJxXl16k7vOw4oXzo|fc_04d35f83dad45bfe016a27fdbcbd648197b582b513dd040b1c", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find . -path '*dynamic*' -o -path '*reports*' | head -100 && find tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0 -maxdepth 4 -type f | sort | head -50", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12937, "output": 1935, "ca