amic-access\nforge/docs/e2e.md:95:The primary fixture scenario is the new/update library dynamic-access path:\nforge/docs/e2e.md:98:   routing, new test scaffolding, source-context preparation, dynamic-access\nforge/docs/e2e.md:108:labels; the primary `9101` fixture remains the default dynamic-access acceptance\nforge/docs/e2e.md:111:For `library-new-request` fixtures that use an already-supported dynamic-access\nforge/docs/e2e.md:115:generated dynamic-access report has 17 call sites: large enough to exercise the\nforge/docs/e2e.md:116:dynamic-access workflow, but small enough for practical fixture runs. Live\nforge/docs/e2e.md:140:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access]\nforge/docs/e2e.md:152:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access]\nforge/docs/e2e.md:168:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access]\nforge/docs/e2e.md:233:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access]\nforge/docs/e2e.md:270:   required by its spec. For the new/update dynamic-access path, verify the\nforge/docs/e2e.md:271:   dynamic-access strategy family behavior (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow) and\nforge/docs/e2e.md:272:   fallback rules (§WF-dynamic-access-fallback-and-failure).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:95:- Script results are written in `output/results.json` (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow, §WF-forge-workflow-drivers).\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:101:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:126:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:386:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:421:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:452:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:459:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:482:see `docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md`.\nforge/docs/architecture.md:105:dynamic-access reporting, metadata generation, or native tracing inside copied\nforge/docs/architecture.md:134:call shared utilities for dynamic-access reports, and native test verification\nforge/docs/architecture.md:153:This boundary is especially important for chunked dynamic-access work. A\nforge/docs/architecture.md:156:§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report. The final chunk is the only one allowed to\nforge/docs/architecture.md:159:(§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:39:2. **Coverage improvement** — increase dynamic-access coverage of\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:43:   ordinary API and execution coverage beyond dynamic-access call coverage, as\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:76:code coverage, not only dynamic-access coverage (see\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:86:dynamic-access coverage workflow defined in §WF-improve-library-coverage.\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:109:| **Dynamic-access report** | JSON written by Gradle task `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` to `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, listing classes and per-class call sites that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:110:| **Dynamic-access exhaust report** | Durable coordinate-scoped JSON state for chunked dynamic-access work. It records the coordinate, issue number, class threshold, processed/exhausted/failed classes, and the latest published chunk PR/commit. It is stored in a stable location derived from the target test suite (for example under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/`) so orchestration scripts can find it from the coordinate alone. It does not predefine all chunks; each resume regenerates the current dynamic-access report and filters out exhausted classes. Specified by §WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:111:| **Chunked dynamic-access workflow** | Dynamic-access generation mode for oversized `library-new-request` and `library-update-request` issues. `forge_metadata.py` owns the class threshold decision and passes the current chunk size to the workflow. The workflow processes at most that many uncovered classes, publishes that chunk, then resumes after the chunk PR merges. PR linking rules are in §WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking. |\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:142:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` — only honored by dynamic-access\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:143:  workflows (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow).\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:170:  If the current dynamic-access report has more uncovered classes than this\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:178:  testing, dynamic-access reporting, native metadata exploration, metadata\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:441:| `RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY` | A chunked dynamic-access run reached a reviewable class boundary and §FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification passed for the current part. The current part is PR-eligible, and the issue must not be resumed until the part PR has merged. |\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781005803241}}
